$ Excel Object Model: split* properties of a Window

The → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Window[`window`] object has two pairs of `split*` properties that allow scroll portions of the same → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Worksheet indepentently from one another.

Setting `.splitColumn` and `.splitRow` create splits that are fixed on row/column boundaries.

The values of `.splitHorizontal` and `.splitVertical` are measured in *points*.

sa:

  → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Window#excel-window-freezePanes[`window.freezePanes`]

  → Microsoft/Office/Excel/GUI/Ribbon/tabs/View/Window/Freeze-Panes[View -> Window -> Freeze Pane]

